data.Name: ExtensiveHeatCapacityPerTemperature
data.Description: Gradient of heat capacity per change in temperature. Note that this is not Heat Capacity per unit of mass (See definition of ExtensiveHeatCapacity)

data.Name: MolarHeatCapacity
data.Description: Heat capacity per mole of a substance

data.Name: MolarMass
data.Description: The mass of one mole of a substance. Molar masses of specific isotopes and those based on average natural molecular weight are both in this unit dimension

data.Name: MolarVolume
data.Description: The volume occupied by one mole of a substance at actual pressure and temperature.

data.Name: SpecificHeatCapacity
data.Description: Supersedes previous HeatCapacity. This is the heat capacity per unit mass of a substance.

data.Name: SpecificHeatCapacityPerTemperature
data.Description: "Gradient of specific heat capacity per change in temperature. The temperature is a temperature difference

data.Name: VolumetricHeatCapacityPerTemperature
data.Description: "Change in Volumetric Heat Capacity per change in temperature. The temperature is understood as temperature difference
